<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                    <head>No. 117.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Roberts</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-11-11"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 11, 1886</date>.
                            (Received December 20.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Chili is about to convert her foreign debt,
                        amounting to $30,000,000 into 4½ per cent. interest-bearing bonds, which she
                        has negotiated with Rothschilds of London at 96 net.</p>
                    <p>By this conversion Chili will save annually in interest $1,455,733.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Roberts.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>